Andrea Villarruel Garca

Bio

I am a Genomic Sciences student interested in evolution and bioinformatics as tools to understand how organisms evolve over time. Throughout my studies, I have developed skills in R, Python, and Bash for data analysis.

Currently, I am conducting a research internship at the Laboratory of Evolutionary Genomics at the Centro de Ciencias Genmicas, where we use microbiological techniques to investigate when, during the divergence of Rhizobium etli strains, the LuxI gene was acquired. This gene is involved in the synthesis of autoinducers that participate in quorum sensing.

Beyond science, I enjoy reading and spending time with my friends.

Education

National Autonomus University of Mexico (UNAM) | Cuernavaca. Morelos

Undergraduate Student in Genomic Science | August 2024 - July 2028

National Preparatory School No.6 Antonio Caso (UNAM) | Mexico City

Experience

Evolutionary genomics, Miguel ngel Carlos Cevallos Gaos Lab. | Undergraduated Research | February 2025 - Present
